        "path": "/books/thawab-al-amal:2:67:1",
        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/23/2/67/1",
        "text": [
          " قَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ص مَنْ أَسْرَجَ فِی مَسْجِدٍ مِنْ مَسَاجِدِ اللَّهِ عَزَّ وَ جَلَّ سِرَاجاً لَمْ تَزَلِ الْمَلَائِکَهُ وَ حَمَلَهُ الْعَرْشِ یَسْتَغْفِرُونَ لَهُ مَا دَامَ فِی ذَلِکَ الْمَسْجِدِ ضَوْءٌ مِنَ السِّرَاجِ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.sayed-athar-husain-rizvi-&-sayed-maqsood-athar": [
            "1.  The Holy Prophet (s.a.w.s.) says, “One who lights a lamp in the  mosque of Allah the  people  of heaven and Allah’s angels seek repentance for that person till the time that lamp is  on in the mosque.”"
          ]
        }
